        "body": "**Missing success confirmation and startup logging before uvicorn.run()**\n\nThe serve() function validates port, handles ImportError, then directly calls uvicorn.run() without any typer.echo() output. Users receive no indication that the server is starting or confirmation of successful startup. uvicorn.run() is a blocking call; after it succeeds, control never returns. This creates poor UX: users can't distinguish between 'server is starting' and 'process hung' without external monitoring. For port 0 (ephemeral allocation), users have no way to discover which port the OS allocated. Missing confirmation pattern contrasts with typical CLI servers (nginx, redis, etc.) that print 'listening on 0.0.0.0:8000'.\n\nRaised by: claude-code\n\nSuggested fix: Add before uvicorn.run(): typer.echo(f'Starting server on {host}:{port}...', err=False) OR wrap with uvicorn config to capture actual bound port and display to user. Example: config = uvicorn.Config(app, host=host, port=port); server = uvicorn.Server(config); display_port = config.port if port != 0 else server.servers[0].sockets[0].getsockname()[1]; typer.echo(f'Server running on {host}:{display_port}')",
